  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are sitting right at the nexus with SPX at 6604 versus the massive +53.1B gamma wall at 6605 and flip strike at 6608, meaning they're actively selling this micro-rally into resistance while the PIN regime keeps them positioned to fade moves in both directions. The gex_surge event combined with spot trading just below the max positive gamma strike creates a high-probability mean reversion setup, with dealers likely to accelerate selling if we push through 6605-6608. Key levels: defend 6590 (max negative gamma where dealer buying kicks in) and watch for rejection at the 6605/6610 double wall (+98B combined gamma).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned near current levels with dealers capping upside around 6605-6610.",
